This project is an independent, ground-up Go re-implementation. It was
inspired by the prior work of the Home Assistant "Daikin Onecta"
integration by Johnny Willemsen and contributors:

    https://github.com/jwillemsen/daikin_onecta

go-daikin2mqtt was developed directly against the official Daikin ONECTA
cloud API, using the Daikin Developer Portal — its API documentation and
mock endpoints — as the source of truth. That integration is licensed under
the GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0). go-daikin2mqtt does not
incorporate source code, translation files, or other copyrightable content
from daikin_onecta; only factual, non-copyrightable knowledge about the
official ONECTA cloud API (which characteristics exist and how they are
shaped) informed this work. All German display labels and other expressive
content in this repository are this project's own.

Our thanks to Johnny Willemsen and the daikin_onecta contributors for
making the ONECTA API approachable.
